The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has said it was confident of winning Saturday’s governorship election having toured all the local governments in the state. The spokesman of the PDP, Oladele Oluwabamiji, told our correspondent that Senator Ademola Adeleke has campaigned in all the local governments and he has been well received. “We have toured the local government. As far as we are concerned, with what we saw, the kind of enthusiasm, and the level of acceptance we received from the teeming populace and prospective voters, we are confident that we are going to emerge victorious in the election,” he added.